beton-mvp/
├── config.ini
├── requirements.txt
├── run.py
├── app/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── config.py
│   ├── models.py
│   ├── routes_materials.py
│   └── templates/
│       ├── base.html
│       └── materials.html
└── migrations/        <- created by `flask db init`

config.ini contains all details: host, port, user, password, database, schema, table.

config.py reads these values and forms DB_URI, MATERIALS_TABLE and MATERIALS_SCHEMA.

models.py defines Material = Table(...) with reflection (autoload_with=db.engine).

routes_materials.py uses Core-style Material.select(), .delete() and .insert() without touching columns in the code.
